![](https://images.squarespace-cdn.com/content/v1/5d56e145f80b7500016ba502/7eba1bce-2df8-4458-96d3-c149c7c128c5/e292.jpg?format=original)

Secret Invasion has come and gone, leaving many MCU fans divided on how to feel about the series, its themes, and the effects it will have on the MCU as a whole. Was it about the capture the rampant paranoia of the comic it's based on or is it a lackluster adaption overall? Join as we break the series down to its messaging, debate Nick Fury's actions and try and predict when CERTAIN people became Skrulls. That plus, our reactions to Sony delaying multiple films, and the release of the Loki Season 2 trailer! Remember you are Worthy!  
  
If you can, please leave us a **_review_** on [**ITunes**](https://podcasts.apple.com/us/podcast/major-issues-podcast/id1321720972) so we can grow our audience and grow as podcasters! Rate us where ever podcasts are found. Don't forget to check out our merchandise! All episodes of Major Issues are brought to you by **ComicBook Clique**, the only stop for the latest and greatest things to come to comic books and comic book media.

